data.name: Sudoku Generator
data.description:
**Sudoku Rules:**
 * A Sudoku involves a grid of 81 squares. The grid is divided into nine blocks, each containing nine squares.
 * Each of the 9 blocks, 9 rows and 9 columns has to contain all the numbers 1-9 within its squares. Each number can only appear once in a row, column or box.
 * A 2D dimensional array (9x9)  will be used to demonstrate a Sudoku's rows and columns.


**For example for a sudoku:**
                                        
        Sudoku Sample           If we draw the blocks seperately for this sample                                 
    [                                       [8,7,9]  [6,2,1]  [4,5,3]
     [8,7,9,6,2,1,4,5,3]                    [4,5,3]  [8,7,9]  [6,2,1]
     [4,5,3,8,7,9,6,2,1]                    [6,2,1]  [4,5,3]  [8,7,9]
     [6,2,1,4,5,3,8,7,9]                    
     [3,8,7,9,6,2,1,4,5]                    [3,8,7]  [9,6,2]  [1,4,5]
     [1,4,5,3,8,7,9,6,2]                    [1,4,5]  [3,8,7]  [9,6,2]
     [9,6,2,1,4,5,3,8,7]                    [9,6,2]  [1,4,5]  [3,8,7]
     [5,3,8,7,9,6,2,1,4]                    
     [2,1,4,5,3,8,7,9,6]                    [5,3,8]  [7,9,6]  [2,1,4]
     [7,9,6,2,1,4,5,3,8]                    [2,1,4]  [5,3,8]  [7,9,6]
    ]                                       [7,9,6]  [2,1,4]  [5,3,8]
    
    - Each row contains all the numbers 1-9
    - Each column contains all the numbers 1-9.
    - Each block contains all the numbers 1-9.
    
**TASK:**      
Create 100000 different Sudokus.

For more details, you may visit https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudoku
